    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="Dj3c3d"&gt;If you don’t want to wait until Black Friday or Cyber Monday to save big on some of Apple’s most popular products, &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24255302/amazon-prime-day-deals-tips-news-guide-2024-october"&gt;Amazon’s October Prime Day event&lt;/a&gt; presents an earlier opportunity. Right now, Apple’s &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0D1XD1ZV3/?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;second-gen AirPods Pro&lt;/a&gt; are down to their all-time low, while the &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BJLXMVMV/?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;latest iPad&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CHX7R6WJ?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;second-gen Apple Watch SE&lt;/a&gt; are still receiving steep discounts on day two of the sale.&lt;/p&gt;
